# migrated from tests/cases/repair.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test repair]
# gen141 (E2): the conversational repair loop. A turn with a referential gap a
# resolver cannot fill does NOT hit the wall — the agent asks a narrow
# clarification, STORES the unfinished intent, and RESUMES it on the next turn.
# Single-turn window: the very next turn answers it or the topic clearly changed
# and it expires. Registered FIRST so it pre-empts the wall and catches the answer.

# 1. An arithmetic operand named by a pronoun: ask for a NUMBER, then resume the
#    real computation. (Numbers set no discourse entity, so this stays "cold".)
> what is it plus 10
< What number should I use for "it"?
> 21
< 31.

# 2. A cold pronoun query opens a clarification; a fresh question instead of an
#    answer EXPIRES the pending repair and is handled on its own terms.
> is it a mammal?
< Who or what does "it" refer to?
> what is 2 plus 2
< 4.

# 3. A teaching answer ("rex is a dog") runs first — it asserts the fact AND sets
#    the discourse entity — so the stored pronoun now resolves by coreference and
#    the ORIGINAL question is answered for real.
> every dog is a mammal
< Learned rule: mammal(X) :- dog(X).
> is it a mammal?
< Who or what does "it" refer to?
> rex is a dog
< Yes.

# 4. With a referent now available, a pronoun resolves directly — repair stays out
#    of the way and the normal path answers honestly (no clarification loop).
> is it an animal?
< I don't know about animal.

